    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "ABOUT THE COMPANY\n\nAt Thrill Labs, we're not just building a gaming company; we're creating a global sensation. We are the innovative force behind Thrill.com http://Thrill.com, a groundbreaking crypto gaming venture set to launch soon! Our mission? To build the world’s most epic gaming brand and craft magical experiences for millions of users. Backed by a world-class team, we’re here to redefine the future of gaming.﻿\n\nAbout the role\n\nWe are searching for an Engineering Manager to manage one of our fast-growing engineering teams. In this role, you will be responsible for guiding and mentoring engineers, driving technical excellence, and overseeing the end-to-end delivery of innovative, scalable solutions.\n\nYour leadership will be instrumental in shaping the processes and culture of the engineering team, driving high-quality deliverables in an agile environment. You will ensure efficient collaboration across teams, and build systems that can support our ambitious vision.\n\nWhat You’ll Be Doing:\n\n - Lead and Mentor: Guide a team of engineers by providing direction, support, and professional growth opportunities.\n\n - Drive Technical Excellence: Establish and uphold high coding and performance standards, encouraging best practices across the team.\n\n - Stakeholder Collaboration: Partner with product, design, and business teams to shape technical solutions that meet business goals.\n\n - Process Optimization: Implement efficient development processes, CI/CD pipelines, and scalable practices to maximize productivity and quality.\n\n - Troubleshoot Complex Challenges: Resolve technical and operational issues swiftly, ensuring minimal disruption to product delivery.\n\nWhat You’ll Need:\n\n - 8+ years of software engineering experience, with at least 3 years in a team management role.\n\n - Still hands on technical and able to code in Java or in one of the frontend technologies.\n\n - Proven track record in leading teams that design and deliver large-scale, distributed systems.\n\n - Solid experience in backend or frontend technologies including Java, Postgres, Kafka, and Redis, or React, Angular and Svelte.\n\n - Practical experience with AWS is a big plus.\n\n - Experience with CI/CD pipelines and DevOps practices.\n\n - Excellent communication skills, with the ability to articulate technical concepts to various stakeholders, both technical and non-technical.\n\n - Ability to set and achieve strategic goals, adapting swiftly to changing priorities.\n\n - English level - C1 or equivalent.\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\nAt Thrill Labs, you’ll have the unique opportunity to shape the future of product development, working with a team of innovators who are driven to push boundaries. This isn’t just another job; it’s a chance to make an impact on a global stage. If you're ready to lead, innovate, and inspire, we want to hear from you.",
